The paper deals with predicting the quality of product titles using deep and shallow learning approaches. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as word embeddings and LSTMs, which are commonly used in the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves boosting techniques and feature engineering, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with image classification (cs.CV) and attention mechanisms (cs.AI), which are also relevant sub-categories.
